Review.Titre: Excellent service, out of date product data resulted in product unfit for purpose [ would not meet code ]
Review.Contenu: Mr Supply has a good web site and good products.And it has good service and fast delivery.The problem with my order is that the product delivered, a Murray 125 AMP main lug load center, was not the product that was specified on the web page.The Web page listed as a feature "Straight-in wired, bolt-on main breaker for 100-225 amps". This was for the older pre-"series A" load enters.The product delivered was a series A load center. Apparently the older panels are no longer available after Siemens acquired Murray.The series A load center is not up gradable to main breaker . I require a main breaker to have a means of disconnect in a separate building.The Murray product listing on the site still needs updating, and the pictures of the products still apparently need updating.Mr supply support went out of their way to send me info on an alternate product that turned out to also not be up gradable. For this I thank them, and it shoes their good customer support.If the product had been what was described on the Website, I would have given a Five star review.I would order for Mr Supply again, after verifying the the product shown is current.The big issue here is that Siemens did not clearly show/document the change.It is not clear from the Siemens site when the change occurred or that purchasers should very product versions and functionality. Multiple other suppliers are also affected by this change in product style By Murray /Siemens.
